  Word(id: '6-1088', korean: '벽화', english: 'mural', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'noun', example: '고구려 고분 벽화가 역사적 가치가 높습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Goguryeo tomb murals have high historical value.', pronunciation: 'byeokhwa', category: 'Art & Aesthetics'),
  Word(id: '6-1089', korean: '공예', english: 'craft; craftsmanship', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'noun', example: '전통 공예가 현대적으로 재해석되고 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Traditional crafts are being reinterpreted in modern ways.', pronunciation: 'gongye', category: 'Art & Aesthetics'),
  Word(id: '6-1090', korean: '아름다움', english: 'beauty', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'noun', example: '아름다움에 대한 기준은 시대에 따라 변합니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Standards of beauty change with the times.', pronunciation: 'areumdaum', category: 'Art & Aesthetics'),
  Word(id: '6-1091', korean: '한편', english: 'meanwhile; on the other hand', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '경제는 성장하고 있습니다. 한편, 실업률도 증가하고 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'The economy is growing. Meanwhile, the unemployment rate is also increasing.', pronunciation: 'hanpyeon', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1092', korean: '더욱이', english: 'moreover; furthermore', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '비용이 절감되었습니다. 더욱이 품질도 향상되었습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Costs were reduced. Moreover, quality also improved.', pronunciation: 'deoogi', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1093', korean: '게다가', english: 'besides; in addition', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '비가 내렸습니다. 게다가 바람도 강했습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'It rained. In addition, the wind was also strong.', pronunciation: 'gedaga', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1094', korean: '뿐만 아니라', english: 'not only... but also', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '이 정책은 경제뿐만 아니라 환경에도 영향을 미칩니다.', exampleTranslation: 'This policy affects not only the economy but also the environment.', pronunciation: 'ppunman anira', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1095', korean: '마찬가지로', english: 'likewise; similarly', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '한국과 마찬가지로 일본도 고령화 문제를 겪고 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Like Korea, Japan is also experiencing aging problems.', pronunciation: 'machangajiro', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1096', korean: '반면에', english: 'on the other hand; whereas', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '수출은 증가했습니다. 반면에 내수는 위축되었습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Exports increased. On the other hand, domestic demand contracted.', pronunciation: 'banmyeone', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1097', korean: '그럼에도 불구하고', english: 'nevertheless; despite that', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '많은 어려움이 있었습니다. 그럼에도 불구하고 목표를 달성했습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'There were many difficulties. Nevertheless, the goal was achieved.', pronunciation: 'geureomedo bulguhago', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1098', korean: '따라서', english: 'therefore; consequently', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '수요가 증가했습니다. 따라서 가격도 상승했습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Demand increased. Therefore, prices also rose.', pronunciation: 'ttaraseo', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1099', korean: '그러므로', english: 'therefore; hence', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '증거가 충분합니다. 그러므로 결론을 내릴 수 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'The evidence is sufficient. Therefore, a conclusion can be drawn.', pronunciation: 'geureomeuro', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1100', korean: '결국', english: 'in the end; ultimately', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '오랜 논의 끝에 결국 합의에 도달했습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'After long discussions, an agreement was ultimately reached.', pronunciation: 'gyeolguk', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1101', korean: '요컨대', english: 'in short; to summarize', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '요컨대 이 사업은 경제적으로 타당합니다.', exampleTranslation: 'In short, this project is economically viable.', pronunciation: 'yokeondae', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1102', korean: '즉', english: 'namely; that is to say', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '그는 전문가, 즉 이 분야의 권위자입니다.', exampleTranslation: 'He is an expert, that is to say, an authority in this field.', pronunciation: 'jeuk', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1103', korean: '다시 말해', english: 'in other words', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '이 결과는 실패입니다. 다시 말해 목표에 미달했습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'This result is a failure. In other words, it fell short of the goal.', pronunciation: 'dasi malhae', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1104', korean: '예를 들어', english: 'for example', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '다양한 재생에너지가 있습니다. 예를 들어 태양열과 풍력이 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'There are various renewable energies. For example, solar and wind power.', pronunciation: 'yereul deureo', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1105', korean: '구체적으로', english: 'specifically; concretely', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '구체적으로 어떤 방법을 사용할 것인지 설명하겠습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'I will explain specifically what methods will be used.', pronunciation: 'guchejeogero', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1106', korean: '특히', english: 'especially; particularly', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '이 정책은 특히 젊은 세대에게 큰 영향을 미칩니다.', exampleTranslation: 'This policy particularly has a great impact on the younger generation.', pronunciation: 'teukhi', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1107', korean: '물론', english: 'of course; needless to say', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '물론 이 방법에도 한계가 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Of course, this method also has limitations.', pronunciation: 'mullon', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1108', korean: '비록', english: 'although; even though', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '비록 어렵지만 포기하지 않겠습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Although it is difficult, I will not give up.', pronunciation: 'birok', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1109', korean: '설령', english: 'even if; even supposing', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '설령 실패하더라도 도전할 가치가 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Even if we fail, it is worth the challenge.', pronunciation: 'seollyeong', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1110', korean: '가령', english: 'for instance; supposing', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '가령 이 계획이 실패한다면 어떻게 할 것입니까?', exampleTranslation: 'Supposing this plan fails, what would you do?', pronunciation: 'garyeong', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1111', korean: '결론적으로', english: 'in conclusion', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '결론적으로 이 정책은 재검토가 필요합니다.', exampleTranslation: 'In conclusion, this policy needs to be reconsidered.', pronunciation: 'gyeolronjeogero', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1112', korean: '종합하면', english: 'to sum up; in summary', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '종합하면 이번 프로젝트는 성공적이었습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'To sum up, this project was successful.', pronunciation: 'jonghabamyeon', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1113', korean: '그에 반해', english: 'in contrast to that', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '선진국은 안정적입니다. 그에 반해 개도국은 불안정합니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Developed countries are stable. In contrast, developing countries are unstable.', pronunciation: 'geu-e banhae', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1114', korean: '이에 따라', english: 'accordingly; in accordance with', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '법률이 개정되었습니다. 이에 따라 제도도 변경됩니다.', exampleTranslation: 'The law was revised. Accordingly, the system will also change.', pronunciation: 'ie ttara', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1115', korean: '한편으로는', english: 'on one hand', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '한편으로는 경제가 성장하고, 다른 한편으로는 환경이 악화되고 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'On one hand the economy is growing, and on the other hand the environment is deteriorating.', pronunciation: 'hanpyeoneureoneun', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1116', korean: '아울러', english: 'in addition; together with', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '환경 보호와 아울러 경제 발전도 추구해야 합니다.', exampleTranslation: 'In addition to environmental protection, economic development must also be pursued.', pronunciation: 'aulleo', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1117', korean: '나아가', english: 'furthermore; going further', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '교육 개혁을 넘어 나아가 사회 전반의 변화가 필요합니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Beyond education reform, changes throughout society are needed.', pronunciation: 'naaga', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1118', korean: '그로 인해', english: 'as a result of that', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '기후변화가 심화되고 있습니다. 그로 인해 자연재해가 증가하고 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Climate change is intensifying. As a result, natural disasters are increasing.', pronunciation: 'geuro inhae', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1119', korean: '달리 말하면', english: 'to put it differently', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '이 이론은 보편적입니다. 달리 말하면 모든 상황에 적용됩니다.', exampleTranslation: 'This theory is universal. To put it differently, it applies to all situations.', pronunciation: 'dalli malhamyeon', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1120', korean: '이와 같이', english: 'like this; in this way', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '이와 같이 많은 연구가 이루어져 왔습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'In this way, much research has been conducted.', pronunciation: 'iwa gachi', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1121', korean: '이상에서 살펴본 바와 같이', english: 'as examined above', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '이상에서 살펴본 바와 같이 이 문제는 복합적입니다.', exampleTranslation: 'As examined above, this problem is complex.', pronunciation: 'isangeseo salpyeobon bawa gachi', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1122', korean: '그런 의미에서', english: 'in that sense', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '그런 의미에서 교육의 역할이 더욱 중요해집니다.', exampleTranslation: 'In that sense, the role of education becomes even more important.', pronunciation: 'geureon uimieseo', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1123', korean: '전반적으로', english: 'overall; in general', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '전반적으로 이번 정책은 긍정적인 평가를 받고 있습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Overall, this policy is receiving positive evaluations.', pronunciation: 'jeonbanjeogero', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1124', korean: '대체로', english: 'on the whole; generally', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '대체로 참가자들이 만족스러운 반응을 보였습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'On the whole, participants showed satisfactory responses.', pronunciation: 'daechero', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1125', korean: '원래', english: 'originally; by nature', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '이 건물은 원래 학교로 사용되었습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'This building was originally used as a school.', pronunciation: 'wollae', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1126', korean: '우선', english: 'first of all; primarily', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '우선 기본적인 원칙을 확인하겠습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'First of all, I will confirm the basic principles.', pronunciation: 'useon', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1127', korean: '다음으로', english: 'next; secondly', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '다음으로 구체적인 방안을 논의하겠습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Next, we will discuss specific measures.', pronunciation: 'daeumero', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1128', korean: '끝으로', english: 'lastly; finally', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '끝으로 향후 과제에 대해 말씀드리겠습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Lastly, I will speak about future tasks.', pronunciation: 'kkeutero', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1129', korean: '그렇다면', english: 'if so; in that case', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '비용이 문제라면, 그렇다면 다른 방법을 찾아봅시다.', exampleTranslation: 'If cost is the issue, then let', pronunciation: 'geureotamyeon', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1130', korean: '그런데도', english: 'and yet; even so', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '경고를 받았습니다. 그런데도 같은 실수를 반복했습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'A warning was received. And yet, the same mistake was repeated.', pronunciation: 'geureondedo', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1131', korean: '어쨌든', english: 'anyway; in any case', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'adverb', example: '과정이 어땠든 어쨌든 결과는 좋았습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'However the process went, in any case, the result was good.', pronunciation: 'eojjaetteun', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1132', korean: '바꿔 말하면', english: 'to put it another way', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '이것은 실패입니다. 바꿔 말하면 기대에 미치지 못했습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'This is a failure. To put it another way, it did not meet expectations.', pronunciation: 'bakkwo malhamyeon', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1133', korean: '그 결과', english: 'as a result', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '정부가 규제를 강화했습니다. 그 결과 위반 건수가 감소했습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'The government strengthened regulations. As a result, the number of violations decreased.', pronunciation: 'geu gyeolgwa', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1134', korean: '이에 비해', english: 'compared to this', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '작년에 비해 올해 성과가 크게 향상되었습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Compared to last year, this year', pronunciation: 'ie bihae', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1135', korean: '이를 위해', english: 'for this purpose; to this end', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '환경 보호가 필요합니다. 이를 위해 새로운 법률이 제정되었습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Environmental protection is needed. To this end, new laws have been enacted.', pronunciation: 'ireul wihae', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1136', korean: '이와 더불어', english: 'along with this; in addition to this', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '기술 발전과 이와 더불어 인재 양성도 중요합니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Along with technological advancement, talent development is also important.', pronunciation: 'iwa deobulleo', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
  Word(id: '6-1137', korean: '이와 반대로', english: 'contrary to this; conversely', level: 6, partOfSpeech: 'expression', example: '수출은 증가했습니다. 이와 반대로 수입은 감소했습니다.', exampleTranslation: 'Exports increased. Conversely, imports decreased.', pronunciation: 'iwa bandaero', category: 'Advanced Grammar/Connectors'),
